---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import ActivityPage from "../../components/ActivityPage";
import TripItineraryPage from "../../components/TripItineraryPage";
import eagle from "../../assets/images/activities/wildlife/eagle-birdwatching .webp";
import peacock from "../../assets/images/activities/wildlife/peacock.webp";
import deer from "../../assets/images/activities/wildlife/deer.webp";

const overview = `This itinerary combines the best of Nepal’s hills and wetlands, taking you from the cloud forests of Kathmandu to the bird-rich marshes of Koshi Tappu. It is designed for serious birders and nature enthusiasts, focusing on diverse habitats that host over 500 species. Key targets include Nepal’s endemic Spiny Babbler in the hills and the endangered Bengal Florican in the lowlands. The trip offers a perfect blend of hiking, boating, and jeep safaris to maximize sighting opportunities.`;

const highlights = [
    {
        title: "The Endemic",
        description:
            "Search for the Spiny Babbler, found only in Nepal, within the forests of Shivapuri.",
    },
    {
        title: "Phulchowki’s Diversity",
        description:
            "Explore the Kathmandu Valley’s richest birding site for Himalayan Cutias and Kalij Pheasants.",
    },
    {
        title: "Koshi’s Waterfowl",
        description:
            "Witness massive flocks of wintering ducks and geese at Nepal's premier Ramsar site.",
    },
    {
        title: "Rare Grassland Birds",
        description:
            "Track the critically endangered Bengal Florican and Swamp Francolin in Koshi’s grasslands.",
    },
    {
        title: "River Wildlife",
        description:
            "Enjoy a boat safari to spot Wild Water Buffaloes and the elusive Gangetic River Dolphin.",
    },
    {
        title: "Barrage Birding",
        description:
            "Visit the Koshi Barrage for sightings of Ibisbills, Indian Skimmers, and diverse raptors.",
    },
];

const itinerary = [
    {
        day: "Day 1",
        title: "Arrival in Kathmandu and transfer to hotel",
        description:
            "Upon arrival at Tribhuvan International Airport, you will be transferred to your hotel. Depending on your arrival time, enjoy a light introductory birdwalk in the hotel gardens or nearby green pockets. Kathmandu’s urban flora often hosts common species like the Oriental Magpie-Robin, Red-vented Bulbul, and Spotted Owlet, providing a gentle start to your ornithological journey while you rest and prepare for the days ahead.",
    },
    {
        day: "Day 2",
        title: "Drive to Phulchowki Hill",
        description:
            "The Cloud Forest Depart early for Phulchowki, the Kathmandu Valley’s highest peak (2,762m) and premier birding site. Descending from the top, the oak and rhododendron forests are alive with activity. Scan for the spectacular Himalayan Cutia, Kalij Pheasant, and Red-billed Leiothrix. The diverse altitude range here attracts mixed hunting flocks of warblers, yuhinas, and babblers. Keep an eye out for the rare Yellow-browed Tit and various laughingthrushes in the dense undergrowth.",
    },
    {
        day: "Day 3",
        title: "Shivapuri National Park",
        description:
            "Seeking the Endemic Head to the northern rim of the valley to Shivapuri Nagarjun National Park. The primary objective today is spotting Nepal’s only endemic bird, the Spiny Babbler, often heard singing in the scrub. The park’s watershed forests also host Hoary-throated Barwings, White-collared Blackbirds, and colorful sunbirds. Enjoy a packed lunch amidst the sounds of nature, with chances of seeing raptors like the Besra or Mountain Hawk-Eagle soaring above the canopy.",
    },
    {
        day: "Day 4",
        title: "Fly to the Lowlands",
        description:
            "Koshi Tappu Take a scenic morning flight to Biratnagar and drive to Koshi Tappu Wildlife Reserve, a Ramsar site in the eastern Terai. As the landscape changes to flatlands and marshes, the birdlife transforms dramatically. After checking into your camp, spend the evening searching for the reserve’s specialties, including the Swamp Francolin and various owl species like the Brown Fish Owl. The sunset over the wetlands offers a magical backdrop for your first lowland sightings.",
    },
    {
        day: "Day 5",
        title: "Wetlands & River Safari",
        description:
            "Devote the day to exploring the Sapta Koshi River by boat and foot. This area is a haven for wintering waterfowl, including Ruddy Shelducks, Bar-headed Geese, and Falcated Ducks. The sandbanks serve as resting spots for waders and terns. Keep your binoculars trained on the riverbanks for the endangered Wild Water Buffalo (Arna) and potentially the smooth-coated otter. The peaceful boat ride allows for close-up photography of kingfishers and herons.",
    },
    {
        day: "Day 6",
        title: "Grasslands & Jeep Safari",
        description:
            "Explore the vast grasslands of the reserve by jeep. This habitat is critical for the critically endangered Bengal Florican, a top target for many birders. The tall grasses also hide rare species like the Bristled Grassbird and Hodgson’s Bushchat. Your guide will help distinguish the calls of various prinias and warblers. In the open areas, look for raptors such as the Pied Harrier and Grey-headed Fish Eagle hunting over the plains.",
    },
    {
        day: "Day 7",
        title: "Koshi Barrage & Bird Sanctuary",
        description:
            "Visit the Koshi Barrage area, a hotspot for aquatic birds. The large expanse of water attracts rare gulls, terns, and the majestic Black-necked Stork. In winter, scan for the unique Ibisbill on the stony riverbeds. This area is also one of the few places in Nepal to spot the Gangetic River Dolphin surfacing. The sheer number of cormorants, egrets, and darters here is a spectacle in itself.",
    },
    {
        day: "Day 8",
        title: "Buffer Zone & Community Forests",
        description:
            "Spend the day birding in the buffer zones and nearby community forests. These edge habitats are excellent for spotting woodpeckers, bee-eaters, and flycatchers. Walk through local villages to see how nature coexists with rural life, often spotting weavers and buntings in the agricultural fields. A final evening walk offers a last chance to tick off any missed nocturnal species like the Jungle Nightjar or Indian Nightjar.",
    },
    {
        day: "Day 9",
        title: "Return to Kathmandu",
        description:
            "After a final morning of birding around the camp, drive back to Biratnagar for your flight to Kathmandu. Enjoy the aerial views of the Himalayas one last time. Back in the capital, the afternoon is at your leisure. You might visit the Garden of Dreams for some relaxed urban birding or shop for souvenirs. Celebrate the trip with a farewell dinner, recounting the extensive checklist of species sighted.",
    },
    {
        day: "Day 10",
        title: "International Departure",
        description:
            "Transfer to the airport for your international flight. Leave with memories of Nepal’s diverse avian life, from the colorful hill birds of the Kathmandu Valley to the rare wetland species of the Terai plains.",
    },
];

const images = [peacock.src, deer.src];

const features = [];
---

<Layout
    title="Kathmandu & Koshi Tappu Birding"
    image={eagle.src}
    keywords="Kathmandu birding, Koshi Tappu birdwatching, Bengal Florican, Phulchowki birding, Nepal birding tour"
>
    <!-- We will use ExpeditionSpecialLayout but we might need to extend it to support Itinerary rendering or just pass it as a custom 'features' block if we don't want to change the component. 
         However, the user asked to 'add this', implying a new page. Since ExpeditionSpecialLayout doesn't support itinerary directly in the current interface shown in previous step,
         I will adapt it by essentially treating the itinerary as a feature list or simpler: I will add a new prop to ExpeditionSpecialLayout or just map it as a custom section below. 
         
         Actually, looking at 'ExpeditionSpecialLayout.tsx', it doesn't have an itinerary section. I should probably add one to it or use 'TripItineraryPage' if that's more appropriate.
         But the user provided content that matches 'ExpeditionSpecialLayout' style (Highlights, Overview).
         
         Let's update 'ExpeditionSpecialLayout' to accept an itinerary prop, as that's the cleanest way to present this data.
    -->
    <TripItineraryPage
        title="Kathmandu & Koshi Tappu Birding"
        heroImage={eagle.src}
        overview={overview}
        highlights={highlights}
        itinerary={itinerary}
        packingList={[]}
        showElevationGraph={false}
        tripStats={{
            duration: "10 Days",
            maxAltitude: "2,762m",
            difficulty: "Easy to Moderate",
            groupSize: "2-10",
            maxAltitudeLabel: "Max Altitude",
        }}
        client:idle
    />
</Layout>
